    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1965-04-30T06:29:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1965-04-30T06:29:00-05:00" n="280"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d280">
                <head>280. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of Defense</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Vietnam</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d280fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, <gloss target="#t_POL1">POL</gloss> 27 VIET S. Top Secret; <gloss
                            target="#t_LIMDIS1">Limdis</gloss>. Drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_MNJT1">McNaughton</persName> and concurred in by <persName
                            corresp="#p_MNRS1">McNamara</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_WGEG1"
                            >Wheeler</persName>. Repeated to <gloss target="#t_CINCPAC1"
                            >CINCPAC</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_COMUSMACV1"
                        >COMUSMACV</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1965-04-30T07:29:00-04:00">April 30, 1965, 7:29 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_DEF1">DEF</gloss> 1097. This is a joint State-Defense message.
                    Ref Saigon 3552.<note n="2" xml:id="d280fn2">
                        <ref target="#d276">Document 276</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>In response to your request in reftel, decision has been taken to deploy
                        in early May, at your call, three battalion equivalents into Bien Hoa/Vung
                        Tau and three battalion equivalents into Chu Lai; Marine air unit will be
                        deployed later in May. Decision as to deployment of additional US battalions
                        in June will be postponed until later, when decision is required to meet
                        deployment schedule.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>First movement, to Bien Hoa/Vung Tau, will begin 24 hours from time of
                        your call and will reach <gloss target="#t_SVN1">SVN</gloss> within about
                        one day. Second <pb facs="0648" n="616" xml:id="pg_616"/> movement, to Chu
                        Lai, can reach <gloss target="#t_SVN1">SVN</gloss> 5 May. Marine air will
                        close Chu Lao on completion air strip there in mid-May.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Seabees, already authorized, are due to arrive Vietnam in time to begin
                        construction at Chu Lai once Marine battalions in place there.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>You should inform <persName corresp="#p_OANH1">Quat</persName> of these
                        decisions and schedules immediately and work out with him announcement or
                        announcements in accordance recommendation para 4 your reftel.</item>
                </list>
            </div>
        </body>
